                Finance
            Corporation</term>
                (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">國際金融公司</term>) means the international organization of
            that name established in Washington, D.C. on 24 July 1956.</def></section><section id="ID_1438402590704_004" name="s3" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2020-09-24" status="operational" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Exemption from salaries tax</heading><subsection id="ID_1438410946247_018" name="1" temporalId="s3_1"><num value="1">(1)</num><leadIn>A Chinese national or Hong Kong permanent resident is exempt from the payment of salaries tax chargeable under <ref>section 8</ref> of the Ordinance in respect of his income—</leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1438410946247_026" name="a" temporalId="s3_1_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><leadIn>arising in or derived from Hong Kong from—</leadIn><subparagraph id="ID_1438410946247_034" name="i" temporalId="s3_1_a_i"><num value="i">(i)</num><content>his holding an office in the International Finance Corporation; or</content></subparagraph><subparagraph id="ID_1438410946247_042" name="ii" temporalId="s3_1_a_ii"><num value="ii">(ii)</num><content>his employment with the International Finance Corporation; and</content></subparagraph></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438410946247_049" name="b" temporalId="s3_1_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>paid by the International Finance
                    Corporation.<marker role="section-break"></marker></content></paragraph></subsection><subsection id="ID_1438410946247_056" name="2" temporalId="s3_2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content>This section applies in relation to salaries tax chargeable for the year of assessment commencing on 1 April 2007 and for all subsequent years of assessment.</content></subsection></section></main></subLeg>